This week's deal was played by our good friend ^*BGeoff Hampson^*N on the first day of the Life Master Pairs in Anaheim. Geoff was playing with ^*BPerry Johnson^*N when this week's deal was played. The deal was reported by ^*BBarry Rigal^*N in Saturday's Daily Bulletin and has been rotated to make South the declarer.

Geoff Hampson (originally from Toronto, but now living in Los Angeles) is still in his early thirties, but in recent years he has established himself as one of the most successful players in North America. In our opinion Geoff and his regular partner, ^*BEric Greco^*N, are among the very best pairs in the world right now. Geoff has also had considerable success playing with other partners, including Perry Johnson. Geoff, Eric, and Perry were all members of the team that walked away with the ^*BCavendish Invitational Teams^*N earlier this year.

Thanks to the many people who made the effort to e-mail us their thoughts on the new "gray text" feature of the ^*BDeal of the Week^*N software. The response was overwhelmingly positive so it looks like the gray text is here to stay. 

